[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---ROUTING SPEC---[39m                                                              [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m# v1 Routing Spec — `@relay-assistant/routing`[39m                                  [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Status:** IMPLEMENTATION_READY[39m                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Date:** 2026-04-11[39m                                                            [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Package:** `@relay-assistant/routing`[39m                                         [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Version target:** v0.1.0 (pre-1.0, provisional)[39m                               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Roadmap stage:** v1.2 (after core, sessions, surfaces, memory, connectivity [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mland)[39m                                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m---[39m                                                                             [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m## 1. Responsibilities[39m                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`@relay-assistant/routing` manages model selection and routing-mode decisions [39m  [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231macross an assistant's coordination context. It is the layer that translates [39m    [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcost/latency/quality requirements into concrete model choices, without knowing [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mabout business logic or user-facing content.[39m                                    [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mThis package is directly informed by Workforce routing patterns: [39m               [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcheap/fast/deep mode tiers, per-request cost envelopes, and quality-preserving [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mrouting with configurable thresholds.[39m                                           [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Owns:**[39m                                                                       [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `RoutingMode` — the three-tier model: `cheap`, `fast`, `deep`[39m                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `ModelSelector` — given a routing context, returns a model specification[39m      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `RoutingPolicy` — per-assistant and per-capability routing rules; configures [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mwhen to use each mode[39m                                                           [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- `RoutingContext` — the signal envelope passed to the model selector for each [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231minvocation[39m                                                                      [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Cost envelope tracking — per-thread accounting of token/cost budget; trips [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mmode escalation when exceeded[39m                                                   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Latency envelope — per-request latency target; routing selects models that [39m   [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mcan meet it[39m                                                                     [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m- Escalation receiver — implements `RoutingEscalationHook` from [39m                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m`@relay-assistant/connectivity`; applies requested mode changes[39m                 [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m**Does[39m                                                                          [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m… +1569 lines …[39m                                                                 [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231ms strict: no provider SDK ownership, no transport, no product-specific routing [39m [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mpolicies[39m                                                                        [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231m6. specify the minimum tests to write now[39m                                       [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
[48;5;237m[38;5;231mEnd the document with V1_ROUTING_IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN_READY.[39m                     [49m
[48;5;237m                                                                                [49m
